[SN]TITLE[SN]
Japan's deflation problem has not hit all prices

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
For years Japan's economy has been battling falling prices and deflation.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
26 June 2015 Last updated at 04:05 BST
But, some items are getting more expensive. The government has warned that the price of vegetables is 20% to 30% higher this summer due to the lack of rain.
The BBC asked one business owner how that was affecting him.
